          title="Design Principles"
          subtitle="The architectural commitments that keep the codebase maintainable as the ontology evolves."
        />
      </div>

      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
        <div class="p-5 rounded-xl bg-white dark:bg-dark-800 border border-slate-200/60 dark:border-dark-600/60">
          <div class="text-2xl mb-2">🔓</div>
          <h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100 mb-1">Open / Closed</h4>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">Concept types are discriminated unions. Adding a new level (e.g., L3 measured quantity) extends the union without modifying existing concept code.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-5 rounded-xl bg-white dark:bg-dark-800 border border-slate-200/60 dark:border-dark-600/60">
          <div class="text-2xl mb-2">🎯</div>
          <h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100 mb-1">Single Responsibility</h4>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">Each build stage does one thing: <code class="font-mono text-[10px]">build-kinds</code> derives kinds, <code class="font-mono text-[10px]">build-hierarchy</code> derives broader/narrower. No overlap.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-5 rounded-xl bg-white dark:bg-dark-800 border border-slate-200/60 dark:border-dark-600/60">
          <div class="text-2xl mb-2">📦</div>
          <h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100 mb-1">Model-Driven</h4>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">Types in <code class="font-mono text-[10px]">ontology/concepts.ts</code> are the single source of truth. Serialization, UI, and build stages all consume the same types.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-5 rounded-xl bg-white dark:bg-dark-800 border border-slate-200/60 dark:border-dark-600/60">
          <div class="text-2xl mb-2">⚡</div>
          <h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100 mb-1">Performance</h4>
          <p class="text-xs text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">Static generation — no runtime overhead. Vue islands hydrate lazily with <code class="font-mono text-[10px]">client:visible</code>. Pages load in under 100ms.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

